    "sections": [
      {
        "trade": "Permit & Prep",
        "lines": [
          "Pull city permit for like-for-like window retrofit replacement.",
          "Confirm new vinyl windows meet current Title 24 energy requirements (dual-pane, Low-E coating, argon fill).",
          "Confirm safety glazing (tempered) is specified for any window in a hazardous location (near doors, low sill height, bathrooms)."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Window Removal",
        "lines": [
          "Remove existing 8 aluminum single-pane windows and sashes, leaving existing frames in place.",
          "Clean up and haul away debris.",
          "Prepare existing window frames — clean and inspect opening, check for rot at sill."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Window Installation",
        "lines": [
          "Install 8 new retro-fitted vinyl dual-pane windows (insulated, argon gas, Low-E) over existing frames per manufacturer instructions.",
          "Customer to select frame color (white, almond, black, bronze).",
          "Shim, level, and fasten each window per manufacturer spec.",
          "Insulate gap between existing and new frames with low-expansion foam or backer rod.",
          "Apply 50-year caulking all around frame (by city code)."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Trim & Clean Up",
        "lines": [
          "Touch up interior trim — apply primer and 2 coats of paint at disturbed edge.",
          "Clean up and haul away debris."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "notes": [
      "If any of the 8 windows serve a bedroom, verify the new retrofit unit maintains code-required egress dimensions (net clear opening >= 5.7 sq ft, height >= 24\", width >= 20\", sill height <= 44\") — a retrofit frame can reduce clear opening below the original.",
      "Client description did not specify frame color — listed as customer selection per standard options (white, almond, black, bronze)."
